## PROBLEM 

WIFI is connected but websites are not opening,which means that there is no DNS translating domain names into IP addresses

## ENVIRONMENT

WINDOWS 10/11

## STEPS TAKEN

-Test internet connectivity and DNS in command prompt in order to diagnose the issue

https://github.com/sebinatlou845-wq/IT-Support--labs/blob/main/dns%20issue.png?raw=true

-Test internet connectivity with ping 8.8.8.8,once it responds with "reply from" ,internet is working perfectly.ping google.com has failed which means that there
is a DNS failure

-TO fix enter settings then enter network and internet,then enter change adapter options

-After right click Etherenet, then enter properties

-After double click IPv4

![image alt](https://github.com/sebinatlou845-wq/IT-Support--labs/blob/bdc4be89b9481dfc206312dc8fac720de2b52c03/DNS%20ISSUE%202.png)

-Then once you see that your preffered and alternative DNS is set incorrectly you can either enter a correct DNS or 'Obtain DNS server address automatically'







